<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>

	<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
	<!-- TripperDash++ entitlements                                       -->
	<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
	<!--
	  This file is intentionally EMPTY on the free Apple Developer tier.

	  The Wi-Fi management feature (read current SSID, join the dash AP
	  from inside the app, auto-connect when already on a known dash
	  network) needs the two NetworkExtension entitlements listed below.

	  ▸ BOTH ARE PAID-ONLY. Apple's free Personal Team provisioning
	    service will NOT issue a profile that contains them, so if you
	    UNCOMMENT these on a free account the build FAILS TO SIGN with:

	        Provisioning profile "..." doesn't include the
	        com.apple.developer.networking.wifi-info entitlement

	  ▸ Leaving them commented keeps the project building & sideloadable
	    on a free account. WiFiManager is written to degrade gracefully:
	    SSID reads return nil and in-app join surfaces a friendly error,
	    so the app runs fine — you just join the dash Wi-Fi once via iOS
	    Settings and use the manual "Connect to dash" button (the UDP
	    handshake needs NEITHER entitlement).

	  ── TO ACTIVATE (after enrolling in the $99/yr Apple Developer
	     Program) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	    1. In Xcode → target TripperDashPP → Signing & Capabilities,
	       add "Access WiFi Information" and "Hotspot Configuration".
	       (Xcode registers them on the App ID and regenerates the
	       provisioning profile automatically.)
	    2. Uncomment the four lines below. Xcode may also add them for
	       you when you add the capabilities — keep a single copy.
	    3. Rebuild. The green connected-dot, in-app join, and SSID
	       auto-connect light up with no source changes.

	    Full walkthrough: docs/WIFI_MANAGEMENT.md
	-->

	<!-- Read the connected Wi-Fi SSID (NEHotspotNetwork.fetchCurrent). -->
	<!-- <key>com.apple.developer.networking.wifi-info</key> -->
	<!-- <true/> -->

	<!-- Join / forget Wi-Fi networks (NEHotspotConfigurationManager). -->
	<!-- <key>com.apple.developer.networking.HotspotConfiguration</key> -->
	<!-- <true/> -->

</dict>
</plist>
